645
00:42:45,967 --> 00:42:48,003
Speed approximately
70 miles per hour.

646
00:42:54,727 --> 00:42:57,002
Get out of the way!

647
00:43:00,167 --> 00:43:02,601
I want a net put on this
son of a bitch, you hear me?

648
00:43:04,887 --> 00:43:07,560
[Screeching]

649
00:43:34,327 --> 00:43:37,160
This guy's hittin' every fuckin'
thing in sight tryin' to block us!

650
00:44:03,927 --> 00:44:06,282
Uuh!

651
00:44:08,647 --> 00:44:10,797
Aah!

652
00:44:13,287 --> 00:44:16,484
I hope you're insured!

653
00:44:24,607 --> 00:44:27,565
- Oh, well, why not?
- [Engine Revving Higher]

654
00:44:41,887 --> 00:44:44,321
You're goin' down!

655
00:44:59,007 --> 00:45:01,316
<i>[Phone Ringing]</i>

656
00:45:04,007 --> 00:45:06,202
<i>- [Receiver Clicks, Phone Beeps]</i>
- Hello?

657
00:45:06,287 --> 00:45:08,198
[Humvee Owner]
<i>Sie haben meine Hummer gestolen!</i>

658
00:45:08,287 --> 00:45:10,243
I'm only borrowing
your Humvee!

659
00:45:14,567 --> 00:45:16,523
[Mason]
Information?

660
00:45:16,607 --> 00:45:18,438
San Francisco.

661
00:45:18,527 --> 00:45:21,519
Uh, Jade Angelou.
That's A-N-G...

662
00:45:21,607 --> 00:45:23,518
[Bell Ringing]

663
00:45:23,607 --> 00:45:25,916
Welcome aboard, y'all.
How y'all doin' today?

664
00:45:28,767 --> 00:45:31,235
Hang on!

665
00:45:32,927 --> 00:45:35,885
- [Riders Screaming]
- Holy shit!

666
00:45:40,887 --> 00:45:43,924
[Horn Honking]

667
00:45:45,927 --> 00:45:48,077
Whoa-oa!

668
00:45:49,607 --> 00:45:52,485
- Oh, no!
- [People Screaming]

669
00:45:56,247 --> 00:45:58,442
We're gonna crash!
Save yourselves!

670
00:46:03,807 --> 00:46:05,798
Oh, my baby!

671
00:46:09,447 --> 00:46:12,200
Oh, no!

672
00:46:24,167 --> 00:46:27,045
Oh, no.

673
00:46:29,887 --> 00:46:32,640
Oh! Oh, God.

674
00:46:33,527 --> 00:46:35,882
Oh, God!

675
00:46:53,367 --> 00:46:56,803
Hey, man.
You just fucked up your Ferrari.

676
00:46:56,887 --> 00:46:59,879
<i>- [Conductor] Oh, no!</i>
<i>Baby's goin'down in flames!</i>
- It's not mine.

677
00:46:59,967 --> 00:47:02,276
- [Chuckles, Grunts]
- Neither is this.

678
00:47:02,367 --> 00:47:04,801
[Engine Revving,
Tyres Screeching]

679
00:47:06,127 --> 00:47:09,483
Damn! This sucks!
Where's that son of a bitch at?

680
00:47:09,567 --> 00:47:13,162
I'm gonna hunt him down!
That motherfucker ain't safe nowhere!

681
00:47:13,247 --> 00:47:15,715
- [Ringing]
- Chem Weapons, Isherwood.

682
00:47:15,807 --> 00:47:19,117
Marvin, look up
Wolfburg Federal Penitentiary.

683
00:47:19,207 --> 00:47:21,163
The inmate is Mason, John.

684
00:47:21,247 --> 00:47:23,920
- [Tapping At Keyboard]
- Hey, Stan, listen. I'm gettin'
out of this government shithole.

685
00:47:24,007 --> 00:47:26,919
I'm goin' over to Orkin
to design Roach Motels. Cool, huh?

686
00:47:27,007 --> 00:47:28,838
Look, I just stole
a kid's motorcycle.

687
00:47:28,927 --> 00:47:30,963
I'm not really feeling too good
about it, okay? Wolfburg, got it?

688
00:47:31,047 --> 00:47:35,359
Yeah, I got it. All right,
Magrane, Masconi, Masters. No Mason.

689
00:47:35,447 --> 00:47:40,043
Go to February '76. Who was transferred
to Wolfburg from San Quentin?

690
00:47:40,127 --> 00:47:42,118
- [Beeping]
<i>- [Marvin] This is weird.</i>

691
00:47:42,207 --> 00:47:45,882
They got medical records,
they got place of birth... Glasgow...

692
00:47:45,967 --> 00:47:48,003
Uh, but they don't
have a name.

693
00:47:48,087 --> 00:47:50,555
<i>Uh, wait a minute,</i>
<i>wait a minute!</i>

694
00:47:50,647 --> 00:47:54,162
<i>They have next of kin, a Jade Angelou</i>
<i>of 32 Stenson Drive, San Francisco.</i>

695
00:47:54,247 --> 00:47:56,238
<i>[Motorcycle Approaching]</i>

696
00:48:13,887 --> 00:48:15,764
<i>Jade?</i>

697
00:48:15,847 --> 00:48:19,760
No, I'm Stacy,
Jade's friend.

698
00:48:23,687 --> 00:48:26,281
Were you afraid
to come alone?

699
00:48:26,367 --> 00:48:28,198
Yeah.

700
00:48:28,287 --> 00:48:30,596
[Whispers]
It's okay.

701
00:48:30,687 --> 00:48:32,996
I'll be over here
if you need me.

702
00:48:33,087 --> 00:48:37,603
- Last photograph I had of you...
you were about ten.
- Yeah?

703
00:48:39,207 --> 00:48:43,883
Well, I found a picture of you among
my mom's things... when she died.

704
00:48:43,967 --> 00:48:46,765
Oh, yeah? Well, uh...

705
00:48:48,447 --> 00:48:52,838
- Why don't we take a walk?
- I got 'im. Palace of Fine Arts.

706
00:48:52,927 --> 00:48:56,840
Your mother, uh... [Sighs]
Ya know, well, she was very special.

707
00:48:56,927 --> 00:48:59,236
Yeah, she was.

708
00:48:59,327 --> 00:49:03,240
But I don't think we should romanticize
what happened between you and her.

709
00:49:03,327 --> 00:49:05,522
Meeting in a bar
after a Led Zeppelin concert.

710
00:49:05,607 --> 00:49:08,758
Head out,
and I was the result.

711
00:49:08,847 --> 00:49:12,203
<i>Well, I'd like to think</i>
<i>it would've led somewhere, if only...</i>

712
00:49:12,287 --> 00:49:14,118
If only what?

713
00:49:14,207 --> 00:49:17,438
Six federal marshals hadn't kicked down
her door and dragged you back to prison?

714
00:49:17,527 --> 00:49:19,358
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

715
00:49:19,447 --> 00:49:21,483
<i>[Mason]</i>
<i>It's all right.</i>

716
00:49:22,527 --> 00:49:25,280
- So they let you out?
- Yeah.

717
00:49:26,567 --> 00:49:28,398
That's good.

718
00:49:28,487 --> 00:49:31,081
[Sighs]
What did you do?

719
00:49:32,807 --> 00:49:34,638
"I do"?

720
00:49:37,647 --> 00:49:41,242
Jade, I don't have
a great deal of time here.

721
00:49:43,007 --> 00:49:45,646
But I'll be coming back,
and, uh,

722
00:49:45,727 --> 00:49:49,163
<i>- maybe we can... - </i>
- What? We can what?

723
00:49:50,647 --> 00:49:52,478
You know...

724
00:49:52,567 --> 00:49:56,242
you're almost the only evidence
that I exist.

725
00:49:56,327 --> 00:49:58,761
But I don't know you.

726
00:49:58,847 --> 00:50:01,361
That's what I want
to change, eh?

727
00:50:05,367 --> 00:50:10,043
I've rehearsed this speech a thousand
times on the chance that we would meet.

728
00:50:10,127 --> 00:50:12,357
Here we are...
and I'm lost.

729
00:50:12,447 --> 00:50:15,723
[Chuckles]
Well, I don't know how I'm
supposed to be feeling either.

730
00:50:15,807 --> 00:50:19,720
Jade, I'm not an evil man.

731
00:50:19,807 --> 00:50:22,765
If you can believe that,
then it's a start.

732
00:50:26,367 --> 00:50:28,198
Okay.

733
00:50:28,287 --> 00:50:30,403
<i>[Sirens Wailing</i>
<i>In Distance]</i>

734
00:50:38,687 --> 00:50:40,757
<i>Is this about you?</i>

735
00:50:52,287 --> 00:50:55,120
You broke out of prison again,
didn't you?

736
00:50:56,327 --> 00:50:58,795
- Why did you come to me?
- FBI, ma'am.

737
00:50:58,887 --> 00:51:03,244
Your father's working with us.
He's helping us resolve
a dangerous situation.

738
00:51:03,327 --> 00:51:05,318
- He is?
- Yes, ma'am.

739
00:51:05,407 --> 00:51:08,160
[Sighs]
Well, gee whiz, John, I guess
we oughta get goin', huh?

740
00:51:08,247 --> 00:51:10,078
Whatever you say, Stanley.

741
00:51:17,047 --> 00:51:19,242
Thank you for that.
You could've handled it differently.

742
00:51:19,327 --> 00:51:22,558
What do you say we cut
the chitchat, a-hole?

743
00:51:22,647 --> 00:51:26,481
You almost got me killed twice,
and my jaw hurts like hell.

744
00:51:26,567 --> 00:51:29,286
- Good.
- Cocksucker!

745
00:51:29,367 --> 00:51:32,677
If I had my way, you would be shipped
back to Wolfburg in leg irons...

746
00:51:32,767 --> 00:51:35,076
<i>and caged like an animal for the</i>
<i>rest of your natural fuckin'life!</i>

747
00:51:35,167 --> 00:51:36,998
<i>You wrecked half the city!</i>

748
00:51:37,087 --> 00:51:40,716
[Electronic Beepings, Phones Ringing,
Low Voices Chattering]

749
00:51:40,807 --> 00:51:44,038
- [Man]
Give me a hand with the system.
- Now, tell me about the tunnels.

750
00:51:44,127 --> 00:51:47,722
If you know the system it will
take you wherever you need to go.

751
00:51:47,807 --> 00:51:53,165
All right, there's an intake pipe here,
below low tide. Is that our best access?

752
00:51:53,247 --> 00:51:57,445
- Yes, that's exactly where I came out.
<i>- Then beneath the cistern...</i>

753
00:51:57,527 --> 00:51:59,882
There's a connection to the abandoned
septic system. How many feet is that?

754
00:51:59,967 --> 00:52:03,676
Ehh... 57 paces.

755
00:52:03,767 --> 00:52:05,803
<i>Where do we go from there?</i>

756
00:52:08,607 --> 00:52:11,075
[Muttering]
Where do you go from there?

757
00:52:11,167 --> 00:52:12,998
That's a good question.

758
00:52:14,567 --> 00:52:16,398
I have no idea.

759
00:52:16,487 --> 00:52:18,717
- What?
- [Stifled Laugh]

760
00:52:18,807 --> 00:52:21,958
I mean... I'll know
when we're all inside.

761
00:52:22,047 --> 00:52:25,642
No. You're not goddam goin'.
Show us on the blueprints.

762
00:52:25,727 --> 00:52:29,481
I can't! [Chuckles]
My blueprint was in my head.

763
00:52:29,567 --> 00:52:32,206
I was underground
for three days in the dark,

764
00:52:32,287 --> 00:52:35,404
<i>just waiting for the tides</i>
<i>to be right.</i>

765
00:52:35,487 --> 00:52:38,843
But don't worry.
It'll all come back to me.

766
00:52:38,927 --> 00:52:41,282
You're not going anywhere,
Mason.

767
00:52:41,367 --> 00:52:43,198
<i>Wait a second.</i>

768
00:52:43,287 --> 00:52:46,438
Now, this piece of work
might be the only chance
those people over there have.

769
00:52:46,527 --> 00:52:49,121
If he's not going, then why the hell
did we get him out of jail?

770
00:52:49,207 --> 00:52:52,483
- He's smart.
- I got him out to get you
people in, not go with you.

771
00:52:52,567 --> 00:52:54,762
If it's the only way of getting
the intelligence I need,

772
00:52:54,847 --> 00:52:58,283
- then he goes.
- He'll fuck with you.

773
00:52:58,367 --> 00:53:01,996
You compromise my men's lives,
and I'll bury you out there.

774
00:53:04,007 --> 00:53:08,558
Now, Womack... you're between
the Rock and a hard case.

775
00:53:09,847 --> 00:53:12,520
Hmm.
How's your bowling arm?

776
00:53:15,287 --> 00:53:17,562
Dr Goodspeed, the goal
is to take out the launchers...

777
00:53:17,647 --> 00:53:19,603
then neutralize
the VX chemical rounds.

778
00:53:19,687 --> 00:53:23,077
Well, we know the poison's being
kept in the prison morgue from
the satellite thermal imaging...

779
00:53:23,167 --> 00:53:25,681
which is right here;
these colourized dots.

780
00:53:25,767 --> 00:53:27,803
Have you ever actually seen
one of these devices?

781
00:53:27,887 --> 00:53:29,843
No, sir,
but I've studied them.

782
00:53:29,927 --> 00:53:33,203
I should really begin briefing your
guys on defusing and detoxification.

783
00:53:33,287 --> 00:53:37,758
Got a really neat layout here
of the chem round as well as the
rocket, so let's get rolling.

784
00:53:37,847 --> 00:53:39,678
That won't be necessary.

785
00:53:41,047 --> 00:53:43,561
Oh, it's very necessary, sir.

786
00:53:43,647 --> 00:53:45,922
The power of this chemical is way
beyond anything you can imagine.

787
00:53:46,007 --> 00:53:48,567
<i>An ecological disaster,</i>
<i>sir.</i>

788
00:53:48,647 --> 00:53:50,922
Plus, the devices themselves
are complicated.

789
00:53:51,007 --> 00:53:53,475
That's why you're
coming with us.

790
00:53:55,167 --> 00:53:56,998
I am?

791
00:53:57,087 --> 00:54:00,204
You're the expert.
What's your problem?

792
00:54:00,287 --> 00:54:04,360
You mean I'm going...
going out there... under the water?

793
00:54:04,447 --> 00:54:09,282
<i>Well, earlier today you wanted a gun.</i>
<i>Now you're getting a gun and a wet suit.</i>

794
00:54:09,367 --> 00:54:11,278
Have you ever been
in a combat situation?

795
00:54:11,367 --> 00:54:14,439
- Define "combat," sir.
- Shep?

796
00:54:14,527 --> 00:54:17,758
An incursion underwater to
retake an impregnable fortress
held by an elite team...

797
00:54:17,847 --> 00:54:21,635
of US Marines in possession of
81 hostages and 15 guided rockets...

798
00:54:21,727 --> 00:54:24,036
armed with VX poison gas.

799
00:54:24,127 --> 00:54:27,722
Oh. In that case, no, sir.
Excuse me.

800
00:54:27,807 --> 00:54:29,638
[Retching]

801
00:54:31,207 --> 00:54:33,801
[Gagging, Coughing]

802
00:54:33,887 --> 00:54:36,355
- Here.
- Ah, thank you.

803
00:54:36,447 --> 00:54:38,403
[Gasping]

804
00:54:38,487 --> 00:54:40,717
You don't look
too good.

805
00:54:40,807 --> 00:54:43,560
In fact,
you look like shit.

806
00:54:43,647 --> 00:54:47,560
My stomach's doing
hula hoops around my ass.

807
00:54:47,647 --> 00:54:51,242
You all right? I mean, you gonna
make it through this thing?

808
00:54:51,327 --> 00:54:54,285
I don't know.

809
00:54:54,367 --> 00:54:58,645
I always expected something
like this was going to happen
but nothing prepares you for it.

810
00:54:58,727 --> 00:55:01,844
Now I'm...
I'm responsible...

811
00:55:01,927 --> 00:55:03,804
for a whole city.

812
00:55:03,887 --> 00:55:05,764
[Faucet Creaks,
Water Splashing]

813
00:55:05,847 --> 00:55:08,361
<i>- [Turns Faucet Off]</i>
- Look, I know this isn't easy for you.

814
00:55:08,447 --> 00:55:10,642
<i>Remember, you were trained</i>
<i>for this kind of situation...</i>

815
00:55:10,727 --> 00:55:12,683
<i>and believe me,</i>
<i>it'll come back to you.</i>

816
00:55:12,767 --> 00:55:15,361
Besides, you got the best SEAL team
in the country backin' you up.

817
00:55:15,447 --> 00:55:18,439
Okay.
You're right.

818
00:55:19,807 --> 00:55:22,446
I'll be on the wire.
I'll help talk you through it.

819
00:55:22,527 --> 00:55:24,358
There's something else.

820
00:55:26,207 --> 00:55:29,483
It's terrible...
N-No, it's wonderful...

821
00:55:29,567 --> 00:55:31,956
except it isn't.

822
00:55:32,047 --> 00:55:34,163
My girlfriend's pregnant...

823
00:55:35,207 --> 00:55:38,961
and she's...
just flown in to see me.

824
00:55:39,047 --> 00:55:41,686
You keep your mind on what you're
going to be doing out there tonight,

825
00:55:41,767 --> 00:55:45,476
<i>and I'll send someone to pick up</i>
<i>your girlfriend and bring her</i>
<i>here to the command centre.</i>

826
00:55:56,953 --> 00:56:00,582
- Hummel!
<i>- Hello, Frank. Lou Linstrom.</i>

827
00:56:00,673 --> 00:56:04,348
<i>I'm at the White House</i>
<i>with General Kramer.</i>

828
00:56:04,433 --> 00:56:08,108
Uh, Frank, uh, we're havin' a few
problems with the account transfer.

829
00:56:08,193 --> 00:56:10,423
<i>Don't tell me problems,</i>
<i>tell me solutions.</i>

830
00:56:10,513 --> 00:56:14,631
We've spoken to the President,
and I know that you're aware
of his stance on terrorism,

831
00:56:14,713 --> 00:56:18,672
<i>- so what we'd like to do...</i>
- This isn't about terrorism.
This is about justice.

832
00:56:18,753 --> 00:56:21,665
It's about reminding you people
who found it politically
convenient to forget.

833
00:56:21,753 --> 00:56:23,983
This is goin' nowhere,
Frank.

834
00:56:24,073 --> 00:56:28,271
Well, let me tell you what is: 15 VX gas
rockets into the heart of San Francisco.

835
00:56:28,353 --> 00:56:30,503
You've got 17 hours
to deliver the money.

836
00:56:30,593 --> 00:56:33,187
Or be prepared to reap
the whirlwind, gentlemen.

837
00:56:37,233 --> 00:56:39,269
What's the word
from Mojave?

838
00:56:39,353 --> 00:56:43,869
General Peterson can give us no definite
assurance on the thermite plasma.

839
00:56:43,953 --> 00:56:45,830
That is the word.

840
00:56:50,313 --> 00:56:52,269
Green light
to SEAL incursion.

841
00:57:08,753 --> 00:57:10,550
Fall in!

842
00:57:10,633 --> 00:57:15,104
<i>All right. Listen up.</i>
<i>Mr Mason will run point for us.</i>

843
00:57:15,193 --> 00:57:17,024
<i>Lieutenant Shepard will be</i>
<i>attached to his hip.</i>

844
00:57:17,113 --> 00:57:19,627
<i>You breathe,</i>
<i>he breathes with you.</i>

845
00:57:19,713 --> 00:57:22,147
You piss, he helps.
Understood?

846
00:57:23,233 --> 00:57:25,349
<i>Dr Goodspeed</i>
<i>is our specialist.</i>

847
00:57:25,433 --> 00:57:29,984
<i>When he neutralizes the threat,</i>
<i>we launch green flares</i>
<i>and we wait for the cavalry.</i>

848
00:57:30,073 --> 00:57:33,827
Make no mistake, gentlemen,
we're in the fight of our lives,

849
00:57:33,913 --> 00:57:35,904
<i>against maybe the greatest</i>
<i>battalion commander...</i>

850
00:57:35,993 --> 00:57:37,984
in the Vietnam War,
I shit you not.

851
00:57:39,273 --> 00:57:41,025
<i>Any questions?</i>

852
00:57:41,873 --> 00:57:43,591
Let's load up!

853
00:57:51,993 --> 00:57:53,984
After you, ace.

854
00:58:15,033 --> 00:58:17,388
Pass out and activate
the Minicams.

855
00:58:19,393 --> 00:58:21,224
Everything set here?

856
00:58:21,313 --> 00:58:23,873
Minicams operational?

857
00:58:24,393 --> 00:58:26,953
Roger that, sir.
We are on line.

858
00:58:30,753 --> 00:58:34,792
Shep, what's the status on the special
operational gear for Mr Mason?

859
00:58:37,673 --> 00:58:40,585
Let's see, we have, uh,

860
00:58:40,673 --> 00:58:45,303
<i>one quart of kerosene</i>
<i>and a squeeze bottle,</i>

861
00:58:45,393 --> 00:58:49,386
three washers
and waterproof matches.

862
00:58:51,033 --> 00:58:54,184
<i>Use the green flares to signal</i>
<i>when the threat has been neutralized.</i>

863
00:58:54,273 --> 00:58:56,389
<i>Now, this is atropine.</i>
<i>If you come in contact with the gas,</i>

864
00:58:56,473 --> 00:58:59,146
<i>you have 20 seconds</i>
<i>to inject it into your heart.</i>

865
00:58:59,233 --> 00:59:02,031
Don't fuck with me on this.
It may save your life.

866
00:59:05,473 --> 00:59:10,786
<i>I have three incoming bogeys</i>
<i>bearing 2-7-5. Range: 6,000 metres.</i>

867
00:59:14,073 --> 00:59:16,826
FBI Command Centre?

868
00:59:16,913 --> 00:59:19,905
- Oh, I would just love for you
to tell me what is goin' on.
- Nope.

869
00:59:19,993 --> 00:59:22,302
Listen, Stanley Goodspeed
is my boyfriend.

870
00:59:22,393 --> 00:59:25,669
- Actually, he's my fiance. Where is he?
- Classified, lady.

871
00:59:25,753 --> 00:59:28,665
Okay, well you just sit here
and act like a Bureau bonehead, then.

872
00:59:28,753 --> 00:59:30,789
Hey, where are you...
Goddam it.

873
00:59:35,673 --> 00:59:38,107
Decoy choppers commencing
run to Alcatraz.

874
00:59:39,833 --> 00:59:41,869
I just lost one, sir.
I just lost one.

875
00:59:41,953 --> 00:59:44,547
<i>We only got two flying in.</i>
<i>I just lost one.</i>

876
00:59:44,633 --> 00:59:46,749
Shit.

877
00:59:55,033 --> 00:59:58,708
In my day, we did it all
with a snorkel and a pair of flippers.

878
00:59:58,793 --> 01:00:01,751
- Your day?
- Yes, didn't you read my resume?

879
01:00:01,833 --> 01:00:04,711
I don't... I don't know
anything about you.

880
01:00:04,793 --> 01:00:07,261
- I know something about you, Godspell.
- Goodspeed.

881
01:00:07,353 --> 01:00:10,470
Goodspeed,
Godspeed, Godspell,

882
01:00:10,553 --> 01:00:13,511
you never went to
any anti-terrorist school.

883
01:00:13,593 --> 01:00:16,391
So just make sure you don't
get us all fucking killed.

884
01:00:18,033 --> 01:00:20,627
We're going dark.

885
01:00:20,713 --> 01:00:22,271
Night vision!

886
01:00:23,833 --> 01:00:25,949
Raider One has dropped
below radar coverage,

887
01:00:26,033 --> 01:00:27,944
heading around Treasure Island.

888
01:00:29,433 --> 01:00:32,505
Sir, we've got two bogeys
bearing due east and closing.

889
01:00:37,593 --> 01:00:39,424
Decoys?

890
01:00:39,513 --> 01:00:42,311
- Prepare to deploy!
- Good luck, Commander.

891
01:00:47,193 --> 01:00:49,070
Sir, Raider One
is at the drop zone.

892
01:00:51,033 --> 01:00:54,343
Stanley's not a very good swimmer.
I mean, he can't even snorkel.

893
01:00:55,513 --> 01:00:57,822
- <i>Everyone, good to go?</i>
- Good to go!

894
01:00:57,913 --> 01:01:01,462
- Good to go!
- [Muffled Words] Good to go!

895
01:01:09,753 --> 01:01:13,189
All right, so the SDUs
have been deployed,
and the Eagles are in the water.

896
01:01:22,553 --> 01:01:25,511
Major, I want the perimeter patrolled
to the west end of the island.

897
01:01:25,593 --> 01:01:29,063
- Yes, sir. Hendrix,
you lead the patrol.
- Aye, sir.

898
01:01:29,153 --> 01:01:30,984
Let's move! Move out,
move out, move out!

899
01:02:25,713 --> 01:02:29,069
<i>The Eagles are on the rock.</i>
<i>They've entered the cistern room.</i>

900
01:02:35,193 --> 01:02:39,584
Thank you very fucking much, Mr Mason.
You've led us into a room with no exit.

901
01:02:42,593 --> 01:02:44,504
Any ideas, Dillinger?

902
01:02:44,593 --> 01:02:47,107
Figure it out soon.
We're sitting ducks.

903
01:02:47,193 --> 01:02:50,981
- Real tight on time.
- You stand by the door. Until I open it.

904
01:02:51,073 --> 01:02:54,145
I'd like to know how you plan
on accomplishing that.

905
01:02:54,233 --> 01:02:56,110
Through here.

906
01:03:03,233 --> 01:03:06,782
- You're shitting me.
- I memorized the timing.

907
01:03:06,873 --> 01:03:09,023
I just hope
it hasn't been changed.

908
01:03:09,113 --> 01:03:12,867
<i>- You catch one of those</i>
<i>flame bursts, you're a corpse.</i>
- Thank you.

909
01:03:12,953 --> 01:03:16,707
- Commander, you said never
leave his side, but, uh...
- Stand fast, Lieutenant.

910
01:03:16,793 --> 01:03:19,512
Have a nice day.

911
01:03:41,073 --> 01:03:44,702
- Where'd you dig up this guy?
- That's classified.

912
01:03:51,513 --> 01:03:54,186
Clear here, sir.
No motion sensors tripped.

913
01:03:54,273 --> 01:03:56,104
Nothing.

914
01:03:56,193 --> 01:03:58,149
Well, tell them
to stay out there.

915
01:03:58,233 --> 01:04:00,428
Sweep forward!

916
01:04:08,953 --> 01:04:10,864
Looks like he fucked us,
Commander.

917
01:04:10,953 --> 01:04:14,628
I knew it.
That son of a bitch jumped ship.

918
01:04:19,673 --> 01:04:21,709
Welcome to the Rock.

919
01:04:35,073 --> 01:04:36,062
Mason.

920
01:04:37,113 --> 01:04:39,866
That's a no-no.
That's the subway.

921
01:04:39,953 --> 01:04:41,784
<i>That'll drop you</i>
<i>into the tunnels.</i>

922
01:04:42,393 --> 01:04:44,224
Do it!

923
01:05:00,233 --> 01:05:03,589
<i>Sir, the Eagles</i>
<i>have breached the tunnel system.</i>

924
01:05:09,673 --> 01:05:11,743
You enjoying this?

925
01:05:11,833 --> 01:05:15,189
Well, it's certainly
more enjoyable than my average day:

926
01:05:15,273 --> 01:05:19,425
reading philosophy,
avoiding gang rape in the washroom.

927
01:05:19,513 --> 01:05:23,392
Though it's less of a problem these
days. Maybe I'm losing my sex appeal.

928
01:05:27,713 --> 01:05:30,830
We've got seismic activity
in one of the storm grates. North side.

929
01:05:30,913 --> 01:05:33,586
Continue patrolling
the area.

930
01:05:33,673 --> 01:05:36,710
Sweep forward.

931
01:05:36,793 --> 01:05:38,863
Commander, halt.
We've got movement.

932
01:05:40,033 --> 01:05:42,467
<i>They're hearing</i>
<i>sounds above, sir.</i>

933
01:05:42,553 --> 01:05:45,545
<i>Stand fast.</i>
<i>Down, down, down.</i>

934
01:05:51,193 --> 01:05:53,707
West storm drain's clear.

935
01:05:57,913 --> 01:06:01,462
Ninety-seven paces
to the shower room.

936
01:06:05,553 --> 01:06:09,910
<i>The Eagles are now at the</i>
<i>access tunnel. They're right</i>
<i>under the shower room, sir.</i>

937
01:06:15,473 --> 01:06:17,031
Fibre optics.

938
01:06:20,753 --> 01:06:22,471
Something's not right.

939
01:06:22,553 --> 01:06:25,670
I've got a bad feeling
about this.

940
01:06:42,873 --> 01:06:44,352
Quiet.

941
01:06:53,753 --> 01:06:56,187
Motion sensors.

942
01:06:56,273 --> 01:06:59,902
- Beam's cutting across manhole covers.
- Deal with it.

943
01:07:05,113 --> 01:07:08,901
<i>Commander, the beam is hitting</i>
<i>some sort of reflective device.</i>

944
01:07:08,993 --> 01:07:11,587
<i>Possibly a prism.</i>

945
01:07:13,913 --> 01:07:16,063
<i>I want to use a mirror</i>
<i>to cut the beam,</i>

946
01:07:16,153 --> 01:07:19,190
<i>send the beam</i>
<i>back to its source...</i>

947
01:07:19,273 --> 01:07:21,229
<i>and then I'm</i>
<i>going to move the prism.</i>

948
01:07:21,313 --> 01:07:25,386
[Electronic Beeping]

949
01:07:25,473 --> 01:07:27,862
We've got motion on a trembler
in the shower room, sir.

950
01:07:27,953 --> 01:07:29,989
We've got visitors.
Let's move.

951
01:07:33,113 --> 01:07:35,707
Got it. Good to go.

952
01:07:35,793 --> 01:07:39,024
[Indistinct Shouting]

953
01:07:40,553 --> 01:07:42,669
Stand fast.
We'll secure the area.

954
01:07:53,153 --> 01:07:56,509
They're entering
to the shower room, sir.

955
01:07:59,113 --> 01:08:01,422
<i>They're securing the area.</i>

956
01:08:09,433 --> 01:08:11,389
Just sit tight.

957
01:08:14,753 --> 01:08:17,745
<i>Drop your weapons!</i>
<i>Drop 'em!</i>

958
01:08:17,833 --> 01:08:19,710
<i>- Stand back!</i>
<i>- Hold your fire.</i>

959
01:08:19,793 --> 01:08:21,784
<i>Drop your weapons.</i>
<i>Hold your fire!</i>

960
01:08:24,633 --> 01:08:27,067
It's a fucking trap.

961
01:08:28,153 --> 01:08:31,509
This is Gen. Hummel.
Drop your weapons.

962
01:08:31,593 --> 01:08:33,424
<i>Drop 'em!</i>

963
01:08:33,513 --> 01:08:38,951
Anderson here, Gen. Hummel.
Commander. Team leader.

964
01:08:39,033 --> 01:08:41,831
Cmdr. Anderson, if you have any
concern for the lives of your men...

965
01:08:41,913 --> 01:08:44,905
you will order them to safety their
weapons and place them on the deck.

966
01:08:44,993 --> 01:08:46,312
This is not happening.

967
01:08:46,393 --> 01:08:51,626
Sir, we know why you're out here.
God knows I agree with you.

968
01:08:51,713 --> 01:08:55,752
<i>But like you, I swore to defend</i>
<i>this country against all enemies...</i>

969
01:08:55,833 --> 01:08:59,826
foreign, sir, and domestic.

970
01:08:59,913 --> 01:09:04,145
General, we've spilled
the same blood in the same mud.

971
01:09:04,233 --> 01:09:07,031
You know goddam well
I can't give that order.

972
01:09:07,113 --> 01:09:08,466
We're dead.

973
01:09:08,553 --> 01:09:11,989
<i>Your unit is covered from</i>
<i>an elevated position, Commander.</i>

974
01:09:12,073 --> 01:09:15,668
<i>I'm not gonna ask again.</i>
<i>Don't do anything stupid.</i>

975
01:09:15,833 --> 01:09:18,108
No one has to die here.

976
01:09:18,193 --> 01:09:22,345
You men following the general, you're
under oath as United States Marines!

977
01:09:22,433 --> 01:09:24,264
Have you forgotten that?

978
01:09:25,513 --> 01:09:27,583
<i>We all have shipmates</i>
<i>we remember.</i>

979
01:09:27,673 --> 01:09:30,904
<i>Some of them were shit on</i>
<i>and pissed on by the Pentagon.</i>

980
01:09:30,993 --> 01:09:34,030
<i>But that doesn't give you</i>
<i>the right to mutiny!</i>

981
01:09:34,113 --> 01:09:36,547
You call it what you want!
You're down there; we're up here.

982
01:09:36,633 --> 01:09:38,669
You walked into the wrong
goddam room, Commander!

983
01:09:38,753 --> 01:09:40,789
- Stand fast!
- Commander, one last time.

984
01:09:40,873 --> 01:09:42,909
You tell your men
to safety their weapons.

985
01:09:42,993 --> 01:09:45,507
- I cannot give that order!
- I am not gonna repeat
that order!

986
01:09:45,593 --> 01:09:48,312
- I will not give that order!
- What the hell is wrong
with you, man?

987
01:09:48,393 --> 01:09:49,712
- <i>Stand fast!</i>
- Oh, my God!

988
01:09:49,793 --> 01:09:52,830
- Let's waste these fuckers.
- <i>One last time.</i>

989
01:09:52,913 --> 01:09:54,949
<i>You order your men</i>
<i>to safety their weapons...</i>

990
01:09:55,033 --> 01:09:57,501
[Screaming]

991
01:10:01,753 --> 01:10:03,664
Cease fire!

992
01:10:21,953 --> 01:10:24,467
Don't go.

993
01:10:26,273 --> 01:10:28,104
Cease fire!

994
01:10:33,233 --> 01:10:35,269
[Screaming]

995
01:10:36,673 --> 01:10:38,470
Cease fire!

996
01:10:38,553 --> 01:10:42,626
Shit. Goddam it.
Let go of me. Let go of me!

997
01:10:42,713 --> 01:10:44,863
Don't, don't go.

998
01:10:53,473 --> 01:10:55,111
[Yelling]

999
01:11:21,113 --> 01:11:22,307
Fuck.

1000
01:11:32,433 --> 01:11:34,264
It's over.

1001
01:11:43,513 --> 01:11:45,868
[Gasping]
Oh, God!

1002
01:12:14,873 --> 01:12:16,704
<i>- [Beeping]</i>
- We got some movement.

1003
01:12:16,793 --> 01:12:19,751
- Who? Who is it?
- Two of'em. Eagles 11 and 12.

1004
01:12:19,833 --> 01:12:21,107
<i>It's Goodspeed and Mason.</i>

1005
01:12:21,193 --> 01:12:22,865
I knew it.

1006
01:12:22,953 --> 01:12:25,751
I've gotta get a team together.
We've gotta move with the second option.

1007
01:12:25,833 --> 01:12:27,903
What, and invite another
massacre? No way.

1008
01:12:27,993 --> 01:12:32,032
We've got a 60-year-old convict and
a lab rat. I'm telling you, it's over.

1009
01:12:32,113 --> 01:12:34,183
Not for Mason,
it isn't.

1010
01:12:45,433 --> 01:12:49,108
Goodspeed, I'm not
gonna kill you.

1011
01:12:51,673 --> 01:12:54,233
- Where are you going?
- Off this bloody island.

1012
01:12:54,313 --> 01:12:56,224
What? Wh... What for?

1013
01:12:56,313 --> 01:13:00,101
[Man On Radio]
Goodspeed, do you read me?

1014
01:13:00,193 --> 01:13:01,945
It's for you.

1015
01:13:03,673 --> 01:13:05,664
- Sir?
- What's the status?

1016
01:13:05,753 --> 01:13:08,631
The status is, they're dead.
They're dead!

1017
01:13:08,713 --> 01:13:10,544
It's just me and Mason.
Now he says he's leaving.

1018
01:13:10,633 --> 01:13:14,831
That is unacceptable,
do you hear me? Unacceptable!

1019
01:13:14,913 --> 01:13:17,427
Well, there's a problem, sir,
he's got a gun.

1020
01:13:17,513 --> 01:13:20,266
What do you have,
a fuckin' water pistol?

1021
01:13:20,353 --> 01:13:23,186
- No, sir.
- Go after him and stop him.

1022
01:13:25,113 --> 01:13:28,788
I didn't want this.
Jesus, I didn't want this.

1023
01:13:28,873 --> 01:13:31,546
- We knew this might happen.
- Maybe now they'll pay up.

1024
01:13:31,633 --> 01:13:35,592
- Maybe now they won't, Captain.
- Maybe we need to execute
a few hostages.

1025
01:13:35,673 --> 01:13:38,346
- Got a live one!
- Put a bullet in him.

1026
01:13:38,433 --> 01:13:40,264
You heard him, end it.

1027
01:13:40,353 --> 01:13:42,184
Holster that sidearm,
Captain!

1028
01:13:59,953 --> 01:14:01,909
Sir?

1029
01:14:05,193 --> 01:14:10,187
You made a terrible mistake. And more
of our brothers have died in vain.

1030
01:14:10,273 --> 01:14:13,788
Damn you for forcing me
into this position.

1031
01:14:17,113 --> 01:14:19,581
I need to talk to you.
Right now, alone.

1032
01:14:19,673 --> 01:14:21,823
Now you told me
I'm on a need-to-know basis,

1033
01:14:21,913 --> 01:14:27,033
and I'm tellin' you right now
I need to know who the fuck
John Mason is right now, sir.

1034
01:14:27,113 --> 01:14:31,231
All right, you wanna know?
1962,J. Edgar Hoover...

1035
01:14:31,313 --> 01:14:33,952
<i>is head of the FBI,</i>
<i>some say the country.</i>

1036
01:14:34,033 --> 01:14:37,742
It's no secret he kept microfilm files
on prominent Americans and Europeans:

1037
01:14:37,833 --> 01:14:41,109
de Gaulle, British
members of Parliament,
even the Prime Minister.

1038
01:14:41,193 --> 01:14:44,469
I mean, this guy had dirt
on everybody in the world.

1039
01:14:44,553 --> 01:14:47,909
Yeah. I know all
the cloak-and-dagger stories.
Where does Mason fit in?

1040
01:14:47,993 --> 01:14:50,712
<i>Mason was the British operative</i>
<i>who stole the files.</i>

1041
01:14:50,793 --> 01:14:53,432
But our Bureau agents caught him
at the Canadian border.

1042
01:14:53,513 --> 01:14:56,744
<i>Of course, the British claimed</i>
<i>they'd never heard of him.</i>

1043
01:14:56,833 --> 01:15:01,031
And we held him without trial
until he gave up the microfilm.

1044
01:15:01,113 --> 01:15:02,990
But he never did.

1045
01:15:03,073 --> 01:15:06,145
I'm surprised Hoover didn't
use his daughter as leverage.

1046
01:15:06,233 --> 01:15:08,872
Hoover was dead in '72.
She wasn't born yet.

1047
01:15:08,953 --> 01:15:12,468
Today, well, it's
a different bureau.

1048
01:15:12,553 --> 01:15:16,671
So you held this guy without trial
his whole life. No wonder he's pissed.

1049
01:15:16,753 --> 01:15:20,871
This man knows our most intimate
secrets from the last half-century:

1050
01:15:20,953 --> 01:15:25,708
the alien landing at Roswell,
the truth about the JFK assassination.

1051
01:15:25,793 --> 01:15:29,263
And Mason's angry, he's lethal.
He's a trained killer.

1052
01:15:29,353 --> 01:15:34,347
And he is the only hope
that we have got.

1053
01:15:34,433 --> 01:15:39,188
Mason! Mason!

1054
01:15:39,273 --> 01:15:41,503
There are 81 hostages
still up there.

1055
01:15:41,593 --> 01:15:43,470
Yeah. Like me.

1056
01:15:43,553 --> 01:15:46,067
You wanna play tough?
You wanna play tough with me?

1057
01:15:46,153 --> 01:15:48,872
Okay, FBI!
Freeze, sucker!

1058
01:15:50,153 --> 01:15:54,112
- I'll fire.
- No, you won't.

1059
01:15:54,193 --> 01:15:58,471
- Throw down.
- You're not the sort.

1060
01:15:58,553 --> 01:16:00,384
Let's find out.

1061
01:16:03,793 --> 01:16:06,751
I could; you, no.

1062
01:16:06,833 --> 01:16:09,666
Besides,
your safety's on.

1063
01:16:09,753 --> 01:16:13,189
<i>Goodspeed, have you</i>
<i>resolved the situation?</i>

1064
01:16:13,273 --> 01:16:14,467
[Gasps]

1065
01:16:14,553 --> 01:16:16,384
Not yet.

1066
01:16:16,473 --> 01:16:19,146
He's got
all the guns now, sir.

1067
01:16:19,233 --> 01:16:21,508
Shit!

1068
01:16:21,593 --> 01:16:25,905
You're right, I don't use guns
and I don't kick down doors.
This is what I do.

1069
01:16:25,993 --> 01:16:27,870
I haven't got my glasses.

1070
01:16:27,953 --> 01:16:30,990
What it says is,
"Chemical Weapons Specialist."

1071
01:16:31,073 --> 01:16:32,506
That's right.

1072
01:16:32,593 --> 01:16:35,710
I got a lunatic up there,
man, with 15 missiles...

1073
01:16:35,793 --> 01:16:37,590
armed with some
really funky stuff.

1074
01:16:37,673 --> 01:16:43,031
That lying Womack.
You could've told my daughter.

1075
01:16:43,113 --> 01:16:45,581
It was classified.

1076
01:16:45,673 --> 01:16:47,470
Look, I'm in
the same situation.

1077
01:16:47,553 --> 01:16:50,625
I've got my girlfriend in the city
with a baby on the way.

1078
01:16:50,713 --> 01:16:52,704
Look, I can
defuse the rockets.

1079
01:16:52,793 --> 01:16:54,624
I really can.

1080
01:16:54,713 --> 01:16:57,671
But I'm gonna need your help,
and I'm gonna need it right now.

1081
01:17:04,513 --> 01:17:07,550
Sir, this man's weapons
and tack radio are missing!

1082
01:17:07,633 --> 01:17:10,784
Shit, we got a rodent problem.
Flush the pipes.

1083
01:17:10,873 --> 01:17:14,024
There's probably a maze of
tunnels on this goddam island.
Check every access you can find.

1084
01:17:14,113 --> 01:17:15,944
Sir!

1085
01:17:21,593 --> 01:17:23,868
Even if you escape
from the island...

1086
01:17:23,953 --> 01:17:27,150
you can't escape
the rockets.

1087
01:17:27,233 --> 01:17:29,064
So, where are you
gonna go?

1088
01:17:29,153 --> 01:17:33,066
Go where?
What're you gonna do?

1089
01:17:33,153 --> 01:17:36,225
<i>[Stanley]</i>
<i>Show me where</i>
<i>the morgue is, Mason.</i>

1090
01:17:36,313 --> 01:17:38,144
<i>[Mason]</i>
<i>I'm out of here.</i>

1091
01:17:40,673 --> 01:17:44,348
<i>[Stanley]</i>
<i>What about your daughter?</i>
<i>Mason?</i>

1092
01:17:45,633 --> 01:17:48,067
Rodents located.

1093
01:17:48,153 --> 01:17:53,273
The way I see it, you don't
really have any choice, do you?
I don't think you do.

1094
01:18:04,273 --> 01:18:07,902
Move!

1095
01:18:11,073 --> 01:18:12,904
Ooooh!

1096
01:18:29,833 --> 01:18:31,664
They're on to us.

1097
01:18:31,753 --> 01:18:33,584
Burn 'em out.

1098
01:18:36,593 --> 01:18:38,743
This mother's gonna
blow big.

1099
01:19:18,233 --> 01:19:22,067
I don't understand. How could we lose
radio contact all of a sudden?

1100
01:19:22,153 --> 01:19:24,667
We've lost coms.
Still got 'em on locaters.

1101
01:19:32,313 --> 01:19:36,067
- So what's it gonna be?
- What?

1102
01:19:36,153 --> 01:19:39,907
- How do you like your choices?
- I don't.

1103
01:19:39,993 --> 01:19:45,226
- That's what I thought.
- Come on.

1104
01:19:45,393 --> 01:19:48,624
This is the oldest
part of Alcatraz.

1105
01:19:48,713 --> 01:19:51,546
Did you know it was originally
a Civil War fort?

1106
01:19:51,633 --> 01:19:54,466
Oh, really? Yeah, wow.
You know, I like history, too,

1107
01:19:54,553 --> 01:19:58,148
and maybe when this is over, you and I
can stop by the souvenir shop together,

1108
01:19:58,233 --> 01:20:01,828
but right now, I just... I just...
I wanna find some rockets.

1109
01:20:01,913 --> 01:20:04,871
Don't tempt me.

1110
01:20:04,953 --> 01:20:08,389
We are going
to the morgue.

1111
01:20:29,793 --> 01:20:32,705
- You sure you're ready for this?
- I'll do my best.

1112
01:20:32,793 --> 01:20:35,148
Your best?

1113
01:20:35,233 --> 01:20:38,305
<i>Losers always whine</i>
<i>about their best.</i>

1114
01:20:38,393 --> 01:20:42,432
Winners go home
and fuck the prom queen.

1115
01:20:43,833 --> 01:20:45,710
Carla was the prom queen.

1116
01:20:45,793 --> 01:20:49,263
- Really?
- Yeah.

1117
01:20:50,793 --> 01:20:53,591
Locaters have them
approaching the morgue, sir.

1118
01:20:53,673 --> 01:20:56,141
Come on, come on,
you can do it, Doc.

1119
01:21:03,633 --> 01:21:06,101
You must never hesitate.

1120
01:21:28,153 --> 01:21:31,270
I think you're shooting
too close to the rocket.

1121
01:21:31,353 --> 01:21:33,150
Him, but not the rocket.

1122
01:21:33,233 --> 01:21:35,872
<i>Any other news,</i>
<i>professor?</i>

1123
01:21:37,273 --> 01:21:40,663
The rocket!
Not the rocket!

1124
01:21:47,233 --> 01:21:49,189
Aaah!
Uhhh!

1125
01:21:50,353 --> 01:21:52,503
[Grunts]

1126
01:21:52,593 --> 01:21:54,470
<i>[Groaning]</i>

1127
01:21:54,553 --> 01:21:56,828
I got a little something
for ya.

1128
01:22:05,993 --> 01:22:07,824
Yaaaah!

1129
01:22:18,913 --> 01:22:22,952
Uh, yeah, okay, that's just about
the most awful thing I've ever seen.

1130
01:22:24,873 --> 01:22:30,505
Mason... the second
you don't respect this, it kills you.

1131
01:22:30,593 --> 01:22:32,788
Put it over there.

1132
01:22:43,553 --> 01:22:46,192
You've been around a lot of corpses.
Is that normal?

1133
01:22:46,273 --> 01:22:49,390
- <i>What, the feet thing?</i>
- Yeah, the feet thing.

1134
01:22:49,473 --> 01:22:53,830
- Yeah, that happens.
- Can you do something about it?

1135
01:22:53,913 --> 01:22:56,473
Like what?
Kill him again?

1136
01:22:56,553 --> 01:22:59,272
Listen, I'm
just a biochemist.

1137
01:22:59,353 --> 01:23:03,312
Most of the time, I work in a glass jar
and lead a very uneventful life.

1138
01:23:03,393 --> 01:23:05,702
I drive a Volvo,
a beige one.

1139
01:23:05,793 --> 01:23:10,025
But what I'm dealing with is one
of the most deadly substances
the earth has ever known.

1140
01:23:10,113 --> 01:23:12,752
So what do you say
you cut me some friggin' slack?

1141
01:23:20,633 --> 01:23:22,464
[Hissing]

1142
01:23:28,353 --> 01:23:30,264
A really elegant
string-of-pearls configuration.

1143
01:23:30,353 --> 01:23:33,026
Unfortunately,
incredibly unstable.

1144
01:23:33,113 --> 01:23:35,149
What exactly
does this stuff do?

1145
01:23:35,233 --> 01:23:39,146
If the rocket renders it aerosol, it
can take out the entire city of people.

1146
01:23:39,233 --> 01:23:43,431
Really? What happens
if you drop one?

1147
01:23:43,513 --> 01:23:46,346
Happily, it'll just
wipe out you and me.

1148
01:23:46,433 --> 01:23:49,630
- How?
- It's a cholinesterase inhibitor.

1149
01:23:49,713 --> 01:23:52,910
It stops the brain from
sending nerve messages down the
spinal cord within 30 seconds.

1150
01:23:52,993 --> 01:23:55,951
Any epidermal exposure or
inhalation, and you'll know.

1151
01:23:56,033 --> 01:24:00,311
A twinge at the small of your back as
the poison seizes your nervous system.

1152
01:24:00,393 --> 01:24:02,224
Do not move that!

1153
01:24:04,993 --> 01:24:08,508
Your muscles freeze,
you can't breathe...

1154
01:24:08,593 --> 01:24:10,584
you spasm so hard you break
your own back, spit your guts out.

1155
01:24:10,673 --> 01:24:13,551
But that's after
your skin melts off.

1156
01:24:13,633 --> 01:24:15,988
My God.

1157
01:24:16,073 --> 01:24:19,270
Well, I think we'd like God
on our side at the moment, don't you?

1158
01:24:19,353 --> 01:24:23,505
So what I'm doing now is removing
the guidance system chips...

1159
01:24:23,593 --> 01:24:26,824
so the rocket'll splash
down after 500 feet.

1160
01:24:26,913 --> 01:24:29,666
All right, let me have that.
You can let go of it.

1161
01:24:29,753 --> 01:24:32,551
All right, just back away.
Just back away!

1162
01:24:32,633 --> 01:24:36,103
Sir, morgue team
has not checked in.

1163
01:24:38,073 --> 01:24:40,268
Blackbird One,
this is Blackbird, over.

1164
01:24:40,353 --> 01:24:44,904
Blackbird One, this is Blackbird,
come in, goddam it!

1165
01:24:47,073 --> 01:24:50,429
Somebody's still here.
Let's move!

1166
01:24:50,513 --> 01:24:52,743
Rats alive! Close on the morgue!
Close on the morgue!

1167
01:24:52,833 --> 01:24:54,824
Go, go, go, go,
go, go, go, go!

1168
01:24:54,913 --> 01:24:58,144
Frye, Darrow, hustle up.
We got more company!

1169
01:25:01,433 --> 01:25:06,109
[Hummel]
Hold it! Converge
on the morgue! Move out!

1170
01:25:06,193 --> 01:25:09,708
Goodspeed, come on.
Come over here.

1171
01:25:09,793 --> 01:25:12,830
Yeah, I love pressure,
I eat it for breakfast.

1172
01:25:12,913 --> 01:25:14,312
Come on. Time's up.

1173
01:25:14,393 --> 01:25:16,748
There's three rockets somewhere else.
We have to find them!

1174
01:25:19,993 --> 01:25:22,427
Come on!

1175
01:25:39,713 --> 01:25:41,544
Clear!

1176
01:25:43,473 --> 01:25:45,907
I'm too old for this!

1177
01:25:45,993 --> 01:25:48,951
- Where's it go?
- I've no idea.

1178
01:25:49,033 --> 01:25:51,501
Sir, all the guidance
chips are gone.

1179
01:25:51,593 --> 01:25:54,391
<i>Captain, I guess you didn't quite</i>
<i>take care of the rat problem.</i>

1180
01:25:54,473 --> 01:25:55,952
No, sir.

1181
01:25:56,033 --> 01:25:59,309
Well, there are two dead men who
strongly suggest you go finish the job.

1182
01:25:59,393 --> 01:26:01,304
Yes, sir.
Yes, sir!

1183
01:26:01,393 --> 01:26:03,827
[Indistinct Shouting]

1184
01:26:09,393 --> 01:26:12,385
- You really don't know
where this goes?
- No, I don't know where it goes.

1185
01:26:12,473 --> 01:26:15,146
Well, we're picking up speed.
Do you know how to slow it down?

1186
01:26:15,233 --> 01:26:17,064
No, I don't.

1187
01:26:25,913 --> 01:26:27,551
Aaaaaaah!

1188
01:26:29,753 --> 01:26:32,426
Uhhh!

1189
01:26:37,753 --> 01:26:42,065
[Grunting]

1190
01:26:43,993 --> 01:26:46,143
God!

1191
01:26:51,873 --> 01:26:55,752
[Groaning]
Mason! You all right?

1192
01:26:55,833 --> 01:26:59,223
Yes, perfectly okay,
you fucking idiot.

1193
01:27:01,113 --> 01:27:03,104
They're coming.

1194
01:27:03,193 --> 01:27:05,661
- Who?
- The Marines!

1195
01:27:05,753 --> 01:27:07,584
Where?

1196
01:27:56,153 --> 01:27:59,384
[Screaming]

1197
01:27:59,473 --> 01:28:02,545
[Screaming Continues]

1198
01:28:06,313 --> 01:28:10,352
- What the fuck's goin' on?
- Let's cut him off.

1199
01:28:10,433 --> 01:28:12,503
[Screams]

1200
01:28:16,193 --> 01:28:19,503
<i>[Screaming Continues]</i>

1201
01:28:24,513 --> 01:28:27,949
[Screaming]

1202
01:28:32,153 --> 01:28:34,986
Mason!

1203
01:28:36,673 --> 01:28:38,789
Mason!

1204
01:28:58,993 --> 01:29:00,824
[Grunting]

1205
01:29:28,833 --> 01:29:31,108
[Grunting]

1206
01:29:51,233 --> 01:29:55,704
You motherfucker,
die, die, die!

1207
01:30:15,793 --> 01:30:20,309
<i>I'm rather glad</i>
<i>you didn't hesitate too long.</i>

1208
01:30:22,593 --> 01:30:25,790
How do you do it?

1209
01:30:25,873 --> 01:30:31,345
Oh, I was trained by the best.
British Intelligence.

1210
01:30:31,433 --> 01:30:34,152
Come on.

1211
01:30:34,473 --> 01:30:39,228
But in retrospect, I'd rather
have been a poet or a farmer.

1212
01:30:39,313 --> 01:30:41,110
Okay.

1213
01:30:45,073 --> 01:30:48,270
Okay, the President
arrives in three hours.

1214
01:30:48,353 --> 01:30:52,107
His directive is to string Hummel along
until the air strike is operational.

1215
01:30:52,193 --> 01:30:54,502
What's the word
from Mojave, General?

1216
01:30:54,593 --> 01:30:58,825
Same as last time, Lou.
They're going as fast as they can.

1217
01:31:03,673 --> 01:31:04,992
Do it over here.

1218
01:31:05,073 --> 01:31:07,507
On your knees!

1219
01:31:16,793 --> 01:31:18,624
<i>[Hummel]</i>
<i>Navy SEALS, listen up.</i>

1220
01:31:18,713 --> 01:31:20,271
<i>You've got something</i>
<i>that belongs to me.</i>

1221
01:31:20,353 --> 01:31:22,662
Twelve guidance chips
to be precise.

1222
01:31:22,753 --> 01:31:26,871
Let me remind you that there are lives
at stake, civilian lives.

1223
01:31:26,953 --> 01:31:28,147
Speak up.

1224
01:31:28,233 --> 01:31:29,029
[Panting]

1225
01:31:29,113 --> 01:31:32,150
- Speak up!
- Oh! I, uh...

1226
01:31:32,233 --> 01:31:33,791
- Uh...
- Tell them your name.

1227
01:31:33,873 --> 01:31:35,943
My name is Larry Henderson.

1228
01:31:36,033 --> 01:31:37,546
Oh, man.

1229
01:31:37,633 --> 01:31:40,466
<i>And I'm a father</i>
<i>of three, and, uh,</i>

1230
01:31:40,553 --> 01:31:43,306
they've got
a gun to my head.

1231
01:31:43,393 --> 01:31:46,988
You've got exactly three minutes
to return the guidance chips,

1232
01:31:47,073 --> 01:31:48,904
<i>or Mr Henderson</i>
<i>won't have a head.</i>

1233
01:31:48,993 --> 01:31:53,111
Oh, no.
Hey, what...?

1234
01:31:53,193 --> 01:31:57,948
Now, three to go.
You find them and defuse them.

1235
01:31:58,033 --> 01:32:01,230
- Okay? All right.
- All right.

1236
01:32:01,313 --> 01:32:04,828
I'll try and delay Hummel
and give you more time.

1237
01:32:04,913 --> 01:32:07,950
Hey, what about
Mr Henderson's head?

1238
01:32:10,593 --> 01:32:13,391
Okay. What do you mean?

1239
01:32:17,473 --> 01:32:19,543
Okay.

1240
01:32:20,433 --> 01:32:23,106
<i>[Hostages Chattering]</i>

1241
01:32:32,313 --> 01:32:33,462
General.

1242
01:32:33,553 --> 01:32:35,544
Who the hell are you?

1243
01:32:37,313 --> 01:32:39,622
I'm all that's left
of the enemy.

1244
01:32:53,233 --> 01:32:54,666
Bingo.

1245
01:33:03,273 --> 01:33:05,104
Stand easy.

1246
01:33:07,593 --> 01:33:11,791
Thought I'd been
in the service a long time.

1247
01:33:11,873 --> 01:33:13,386
Name and rank, sailor.

1248
01:33:13,473 --> 01:33:16,033
It's Army, actually.

1249
01:33:16,113 --> 01:33:19,788
Answer the question.
And address him as "General, sir."

1250
01:33:21,313 --> 01:33:24,305
Captain John Patrick Mason,
General, sir...

1251
01:33:24,393 --> 01:33:26,429
of Her Majesty's SAS.

1252
01:33:26,513 --> 01:33:28,151
Retired, of course.

1253
01:33:31,913 --> 01:33:34,711
You're a long way
from home, Captain.

1254
01:33:34,793 --> 01:33:37,227
How the hell are you
involved in this?

1255
01:33:37,313 --> 01:33:40,111
I have a unique knowledge
of this prison facility.

1256
01:33:40,193 --> 01:33:42,753
I was, uh...
formerly a guest here.

1257
01:33:56,113 --> 01:33:57,705
Hi, sweetie.

1258
01:33:58,673 --> 01:33:59,708
[Screaming]

1259
01:34:04,993 --> 01:34:07,268
<i>Hey, come back here,</i>
<i>little boy.</i>

1260
01:34:09,313 --> 01:34:11,668
Did they bother to tell you
who I am, why I'm doing this,

1261
01:34:11,753 --> 01:34:13,903
or are they just using you
like they do everybody else?

1262
01:34:13,993 --> 01:34:17,781
All I know is you were big in Vietnam.
I saw the highlights on television.

1263
01:34:17,873 --> 01:34:21,832
You wouldn't have any idea
what it means to lead the finest
men on God's earth into battle,

1264
01:34:21,913 --> 01:34:24,746
and then see their memory betrayed
by their own fuckin' government!

1265
01:34:24,833 --> 01:34:29,543
I don't quite see how you
cherish the memory of the dead
by killing another million.

1266
01:34:29,633 --> 01:34:33,228
And, uh...
this is not combat.

1267
01:34:33,313 --> 01:34:37,431
It's an act of lunacy,
General, sir.

1268
01:34:37,513 --> 01:34:40,107
Personally, I think
you're a fuckin' idiot.

1269
01:34:46,113 --> 01:34:48,069
"The tree of liberty
must be refreshed from time to time...

1270
01:34:48,153 --> 01:34:50,986
with the blood of patriots
and tyrants." Thomas Jefferson.

1271
01:34:51,073 --> 01:34:56,591
"Patriotism is the virtue of
the vicious," according to Oscar Wilde.

1272
01:34:56,673 --> 01:35:01,064
[Grunts, Groaning]

1273
01:35:01,153 --> 01:35:03,303
Thank you
for making my point.

1274
01:35:03,393 --> 01:35:07,625
Where are the guidance chips?
Where are the guidance chips!

1275
01:35:07,713 --> 01:35:09,943
I destroyed them.

1276
01:35:10,033 --> 01:35:12,593
That was a bad move, soldier.

1277
01:35:12,673 --> 01:35:14,664
Does that mean
you'll execute us both?

1278
01:35:21,193 --> 01:35:23,343
<i>[Rapid Gunfire]</i>

1279
01:35:31,073 --> 01:35:35,112
[Choking, Yelling]

1280
01:35:36,273 --> 01:35:39,822
[Screams, Grunts]

1281
01:35:42,593 --> 01:35:44,902
<i>You're lucky that old man</i>
<i>Hummel wants you alive.</i>

1282
01:35:44,993 --> 01:35:46,551
'Cause I'd take pleasure
in guttin' you, boy.

1283
01:35:53,433 --> 01:35:58,348
<i>[Stanley]</i>
<i>I'd take pleasure</i>
<i>in guttin'you... boy.</i>

1284
01:35:58,433 --> 01:36:03,712
I'll take pleasure
in guttin' you. Boy.

1285
01:36:03,793 --> 01:36:05,624
What is wrong with these
people, huh, Mason?

1286
01:36:05,713 --> 01:36:09,672
<i>Don't you think there's a lot</i>
<i>of, uh, lot of anger flowin'</i>
<i>around this island?</i>

1287
01:36:09,753 --> 01:36:12,631
Kind of a pubescent volatility?
Don't you think?

1288
01:36:12,713 --> 01:36:16,945
A lot of angst, lot of "I'm 16,
I'm angry at my father" syndrome?

1289
01:36:17,033 --> 01:36:19,228
I mean, grow up!
We're stuck on an island...

1290
01:36:19,313 --> 01:36:22,225
<i>with a bunch of</i>
<i>violence-for-pleasure-seeking</i>
<i>psychopathic Marines.</i>

1291
01:36:22,313 --> 01:36:24,873
Shame on them!

1292
01:36:24,953 --> 01:36:27,069
[Clears Throat]

1293
01:36:27,153 --> 01:36:30,031
<i>Anyway, I only got one chem rod,</i>
<i>and there's two left.</i>

1294
01:36:30,113 --> 01:36:31,944
<i>Mason?</i>

1295
01:36:32,033 --> 01:36:33,864
Yes, I'm here.

1296
01:36:33,953 --> 01:36:36,592
I was just thinking
how wonderful it was...

1297
01:36:36,673 --> 01:36:39,392
when the inmates weren't
allowed to talk in here.

1298
01:36:39,473 --> 01:36:42,033
Not allowed to talk.

1299
01:36:42,113 --> 01:36:44,263
<i>How did you do it?</i>

1300
01:36:44,353 --> 01:36:48,790
[Sighs]
Nurtured the hope
that there was hope...

1301
01:36:48,873 --> 01:36:52,263
<i>that one day I'd breathe</i>
<i>free air.</i>

1302
01:36:52,353 --> 01:36:55,584
Perhaps meet my daughter.

1303
01:36:55,673 --> 01:36:59,552
Modest hopes,
but they kept a man alive.

1304
01:36:59,633 --> 01:37:03,342
<i>What did they put you</i>
<i>away for, John?</i>

1305
01:37:03,433 --> 01:37:06,152
<i>Oh, that's a long story.</i>

1306
01:37:06,233 --> 01:37:08,224
Well, I'm not
going anywhere.

1307
01:37:08,313 --> 01:37:11,783
When was the last communication
from our men on Alcatraz?

1308
01:37:11,873 --> 01:37:14,023
Seven hours.

1309
01:37:14,113 --> 01:37:18,072
- [Phone Rings]
- Thermite plasma is operational.

1310
01:37:18,153 --> 01:37:20,542
Get me the President.

1311
01:37:20,633 --> 01:37:24,148
Be seated. Gentlemen,
consider yourselves on ground alert.

1312
01:37:24,233 --> 01:37:27,066
If we receive launch authority,
your mission is...

1313
01:37:27,153 --> 01:37:29,872
the complete thermal destruction
of Alcatraz Island.

1314
01:37:29,953 --> 01:37:32,990
<i>The entire island is to be blanketed,</i>
<i>not one square inch missed.</i>

1315
01:37:33,073 --> 01:37:38,067
Eighty-one American civilians
and a number of US Marines
will lose their lives.

1316
01:37:39,833 --> 01:37:45,191
<i>Why didn't you just tell them</i>
<i>where the microfilm was</i>
<i>and create a solution?</i>

1317
01:37:45,273 --> 01:37:49,710
[Chuckles]
The moment they had the
microfilm, they'd suicide me.

1318
01:37:49,793 --> 01:37:52,865
- Some solution.
- <i>You ended up here.</i>

1319
01:37:52,953 --> 01:37:56,184
<i>Which brings me</i>
<i>to another question.</i>

1320
01:37:56,273 --> 01:37:59,504
You broke out... let me see
if I can get this straight...

1321
01:37:59,593 --> 01:38:03,950
you went down the incinerator chute,
on the mine car,

1322
01:38:04,033 --> 01:38:06,593
<i>through the tunnels</i>
<i>to the power plant,</i>

1323
01:38:06,673 --> 01:38:10,222
under the steam engine...
that was really cool, by the way...

1324
01:38:10,313 --> 01:38:13,669
and into the cistern
through the intake pipe,

1325
01:38:13,753 --> 01:38:18,031
[Clears Throat]
but how, in the name
of Zeus's butthole,

1326
01:38:18,113 --> 01:38:20,911
did you get
out of your cell?

1327
01:38:20,993 --> 01:38:23,826
I only ask because
in our current situation,

1328
01:38:23,913 --> 01:38:28,907
well, it could prove to be
useful information, maybe!

1329
01:38:45,593 --> 01:38:48,266
Trade secrets, my son.

1330
01:38:49,913 --> 01:38:51,505
Wow.

1331
01:38:51,873 --> 01:38:54,182
General, two operational
rockets left.

1332
01:38:54,273 --> 01:38:56,867
<i>One at the lower lighthouse</i>
<i>and one on the roof.</i>

1333
01:38:56,953 --> 01:39:00,582
<i>Both of the birds are ready to fly,</i>
<i>sir. General, can you hear me?</i>

1334
01:39:00,673 --> 01:39:03,631
- I heard you, Captain.
- Just makin' sure.

1335
01:39:05,153 --> 01:39:08,031
<i>Should we... prepare</i>
<i>for launch, General?</i>

1336
01:39:09,313 --> 01:39:11,508
I'll handle
the strategy, Captain.

1337
01:39:11,593 --> 01:39:14,187
Yes, sir.

1338
01:39:14,273 --> 01:39:18,232
The hour is approaching, sir.
Just letting the General know
of the time, sir.

1339
01:39:18,313 --> 01:39:20,144
I'm very aware
of the time, Captain.

1340
01:39:20,233 --> 01:39:22,428
<i>Aye, aye, sir.</i>
<i>Lettin'you know.</i>

1341
01:39:22,513 --> 01:39:25,073
Me and my boys are cocked,
locked and ready to rock.

1342
01:39:26,993 --> 01:39:28,824
Mason, where are you going?

1343
01:39:28,913 --> 01:39:31,302
Thirty years ago I vowed
I wouldn't die in this toilet.

1344
01:39:31,393 --> 01:39:36,467
You're not leaving! There's a madman
in there with his hand on a button!

1345
01:39:36,553 --> 01:39:40,182
Shhh. Some sniper's
gonna get his ass.

1346
01:39:40,273 --> 01:39:42,343
Stop moving, Mason.

1347
01:39:44,313 --> 01:39:46,588
Mason, stop moving.

1348
01:39:46,673 --> 01:39:49,904
Hummel won't do it.
He's a soldier, not a murderer.

1349
01:39:49,993 --> 01:39:52,188
I read it in his eyes.

1350
01:39:52,273 --> 01:39:55,822
Read his eyes? Oh, well,
then everything's just fine!

1351
01:39:55,913 --> 01:39:58,985
- I can't afford to take that chance.
- Why don't you talk louder?

1352
01:39:59,073 --> 01:40:01,462
Three minutes to go, sir.

1353
01:40:03,233 --> 01:40:05,986
- They're not gonna call, Frank.
- Oh, they'll call.

1354
01:40:06,073 --> 01:40:09,270
They'll call if we fire
one of our rockets up their ass.

1355
01:40:09,353 --> 01:40:12,265
Sir.

1356
01:40:12,353 --> 01:40:14,503
<i>[Phone Ringing]</i>

1357
01:40:16,633 --> 01:40:19,545
- Hummel.
- Hi, Frank, it's Al Kramer here.

1358
01:40:19,633 --> 01:40:22,431
- How's it going out there?
- How do you think it's going?

1359
01:40:22,513 --> 01:40:25,823
- We're gonna need another hour, Frank.
- You've got three minutes.

1360
01:40:25,913 --> 01:40:30,031
- We have to get authorization
from the President.
- You've got three minutes.

1361
01:40:30,113 --> 01:40:33,344
Frank, please don't do
anything stupid.

1362
01:40:33,433 --> 01:40:37,062
They want another hour.

1363
01:40:37,153 --> 01:40:40,350
That's bullshit.
That's bullshit, General. They're lying.

1364
01:40:40,433 --> 01:40:44,745
<i>They're calling our bluff, sir.</i>
<i>They're playing you for a fool.</i>

1365
01:40:44,833 --> 01:40:49,384
Sir, order the launch,
General.

1366
01:40:49,473 --> 01:40:52,863
Come on, General,
let's be all we can be.

1367
01:41:06,713 --> 01:41:08,749
The mission's
not complete!

1368
01:41:08,833 --> 01:41:10,710
Well, mine is.

1369
01:41:10,793 --> 01:41:13,387
When this is over,
you'll go back home,

1370
01:41:13,473 --> 01:41:18,024
driving Carla and your baby
insane in your beige Volvo.

1371
01:41:18,113 --> 01:41:21,549
And I'll be dead, or back in prison
which is the same thing.

1372
01:41:21,633 --> 01:41:25,865
You're not leaving.
[Grunts, Groaning]

1373
01:41:28,193 --> 01:41:31,947
All right...
I'll do it myself.

1374
01:41:33,073 --> 01:41:35,189
I got three weeks'
weapons training.

1375
01:41:35,273 --> 01:41:39,391
<i>I'll kick the... out of</i>
<i>a platoon full of Marines.</i>

1376
01:41:39,473 --> 01:41:42,192
No problem.

1377
01:41:52,713 --> 01:41:54,669
Major, patch me
into roof battery.

1378
01:41:54,753 --> 01:41:55,947
Aye, sir.

1379
01:41:56,033 --> 01:41:59,787
Fire open control circuit
coordinates to the roof, sir.

1380
01:41:59,873 --> 01:42:02,148
Let's go!

1381
01:42:07,233 --> 01:42:09,224
Laser powered up.

1382
01:42:09,313 --> 01:42:11,144
Oh, no.

1383
01:42:11,233 --> 01:42:13,701
I said, on your knees!

1384
01:42:13,793 --> 01:42:16,068
My name's Stanley Goodspeed.

1385
01:42:16,153 --> 01:42:19,031
I'm a chemical weapons
specialist for the FBI.

1386
01:42:19,113 --> 01:42:21,069
- Uh, glass or plastic?
- What?

1387
01:42:21,153 --> 01:42:23,587
- Glass or plastic!
- Shut the fuck up!

1388
01:42:23,673 --> 01:42:27,109
Because if the winds change
and you launch those rockets,
we're all gonna die.

1389
01:42:27,193 --> 01:42:32,392
- Shut up!
- And you're gonna end up in
a glass jar or a plastic bag.

1390
01:42:32,473 --> 01:42:37,103
So do the math, hand over the gun
and let's go find some rockets!

1391
01:42:37,193 --> 01:42:40,390
I said shut the fuck...
[Neck Snaps]

1392
01:42:44,913 --> 01:42:48,349
[Panting]
You made the right choice.

1393
01:42:48,433 --> 01:42:52,426
I decided I didn't want your child
growing up without a father.

1394
01:42:52,513 --> 01:42:55,710
Hey, the last time I swam
this channel I was your age.

1395
01:42:55,793 --> 01:42:58,671
So I'm fucked either way.
So come on.

1396
01:42:58,753 --> 01:43:01,551
The weapon is hot. I am standing by
for the launch command.

1397
01:43:01,633 --> 01:43:04,989
Man, killing Navy SEALs is one thing...
Is this for real?

1398
01:43:05,073 --> 01:43:07,587
Hey, it's business.

1399
01:43:10,113 --> 01:43:12,627
Access code entered.
Weapon available for release.

1400
01:43:12,713 --> 01:43:14,544
<i>Launch coordinates:</i>

1401
01:43:14,633 --> 01:43:18,672
six, seven, five, four,
five, niner.

1402
01:43:20,353 --> 01:43:22,548
The weapon is hot.

1403
01:43:22,633 --> 01:43:25,227
I'm standing by
for launch command.

1404
01:43:25,313 --> 01:43:27,269
It's affirmative.

1405
01:43:30,233 --> 01:43:33,305
[Bell Chiming]

1406
01:43:33,393 --> 01:43:35,782
Standing by for command.

1407
01:43:43,553 --> 01:43:45,862
I'm waiting for
a launch command, General.

1408
01:43:53,633 --> 01:43:55,624
- Fire.
- Fire!

1409
01:44:01,233 --> 01:44:03,428
Missile loose!
Missile loose!

1410
01:44:08,753 --> 01:44:13,144
<i>Origin: Alcatraz, 67253725.</i>

1411
01:44:13,233 --> 01:44:17,112
- What's the heading?
- Heading 185 degrees south southeast.

1412
01:44:17,193 --> 01:44:19,149
- Speed?
- 300 knots.

1413
01:44:19,233 --> 01:44:21,144
It's headed
right at Oakland.

1414
01:44:21,233 --> 01:44:23,793
The football game.

1415
01:44:25,993 --> 01:44:27,711
Oh, my God.

1416
01:44:49,713 --> 01:44:52,625
Missile radically
changing direction.

1417
01:44:57,553 --> 01:45:01,865
<i>New direction:275 degrees west.</i>
<i>It's headed out to sea, sir.</i>

1418
01:45:01,953 --> 01:45:04,069
Oh, Christ!

1419
01:45:05,473 --> 01:45:09,227
Missile losing altitude.
Falling.

1420
01:45:09,313 --> 01:45:13,750
Falling, 300 feet, 200, 100.

1421
01:45:15,713 --> 01:45:18,466
Bogey detonated under water.

1422
01:45:20,633 --> 01:45:22,669
What the fuck?

1423
01:45:22,833 --> 01:45:26,109
- It missed.
- Well, that's great.

1424
01:45:26,193 --> 01:45:29,549
Extremely great,
but there's still one left.

1425
01:45:29,633 --> 01:45:33,182
<i>What happened to the rocket?</i>
<i>What the fuck happened</i>
<i>to the coordinates?</i>

1426
01:45:33,273 --> 01:45:36,345
What the fuck is going on?
Sir! Major!

1427
01:45:36,433 --> 01:45:38,867
Captain, step outside.

1428
01:45:38,953 --> 01:45:41,547
- Talk to me, sir.
- Captain, step outside!

1429
01:45:54,353 --> 01:45:56,628
Get me the Pentagon.

1430
01:46:08,953 --> 01:46:11,183
What the hell
was that, Frank?

1431
01:46:12,993 --> 01:46:15,632
- I said, what the hell...
- I heard what you said!

1432
01:46:15,713 --> 01:46:19,069
- I'd appreciate a little more respect.
- Cut the crap, General.

1433
01:46:19,153 --> 01:46:21,428
- What the hell are you doing?
- I'm not ready to kill these people.

1434
01:46:21,513 --> 01:46:23,469
- Call the Pentagon. Ask for more time.
- No.

1435
01:46:23,553 --> 01:46:26,511
Do it, Frank!
We're coming loose.

1436
01:46:26,593 --> 01:46:29,585
You're coming loose.
The rest of us are in complete control.

1437
01:46:29,673 --> 01:46:32,506
- We're gonna ask them
for a new deadline.
- Put the phone down.

1438
01:46:32,593 --> 01:46:35,869
- The men are falling apart!
- The men are Marines!
- Are they?

1439
01:46:35,953 --> 01:46:38,751
<i>I wanna talk</i>
<i>to General Kramer.</i>

1440
01:46:38,833 --> 01:46:41,711
- You've been asked by an old friend.
- Put him on the phone right now.

1441
01:46:41,793 --> 01:46:43,784
- You've been ordered.
- This is Major Baxter!

1442
01:46:43,873 --> 01:46:47,104
Now you're being given your
last chance by a man with a gun.

1443
01:46:47,193 --> 01:46:49,104
<i>Put the phone down.</i>

1444
01:46:50,913 --> 01:46:53,222
I thought you weren't
ready to kill.

1445
01:46:53,313 --> 01:46:55,873
I'm warming up.

1446
01:46:55,953 --> 01:46:58,023
At ease.

1447
01:47:06,273 --> 01:47:09,265
They need a decision,
Mr President.

1448
01:47:14,993 --> 01:47:18,781
[Sighs]
These past few hours...

1449
01:47:18,873 --> 01:47:22,991
<i>have been the longest,</i>
<i>darkest of my life.</i>

1450
01:47:23,073 --> 01:47:26,349
<i>How does one weigh</i>
<i>human life?</i>

1451
01:47:27,753 --> 01:47:31,143
<i>One million civilians</i>
<i>against 81 hostages.</i>

1452
01:47:31,233 --> 01:47:34,464
And in the middle,
Frank Hummel.

1453
01:47:34,553 --> 01:47:39,502
[Sighs]
That we have ignored, abandoned...

1454
01:47:39,593 --> 01:47:42,824
<i>or marginalized a great</i>
<i>soldier like Frank Hummel,</i>

1455
01:47:42,913 --> 01:47:46,030
and American boys have paid
for that neglect...

1456
01:47:46,113 --> 01:47:49,389
<i>in blood</i>
<i>is equally real...</i>

1457
01:47:49,473 --> 01:47:51,782
<i>and equally tragic.</i>

1458
01:47:54,233 --> 01:47:56,269
We are at war with terror,

1459
01:47:56,353 --> 01:47:59,789
<i>and fighting war</i>
<i>means casualties.</i>

1460
01:47:59,873 --> 01:48:03,149
<i>This is the worst call</i>
<i>I've ever had to make.</i>

1461
01:48:07,113 --> 01:48:09,581
Air strike approved.

1462
01:48:12,673 --> 01:48:14,584
<i>Red Thunder to Tower.</i>
<i>Request clearance.</i>

1463
01:48:14,673 --> 01:48:17,506
The amount of firepower
they're gonna drop in there,

1464
01:48:17,593 --> 01:48:19,549
This is strike leader.
Prepared to go.

1465
01:48:19,633 --> 01:48:21,942
it'll be over in a few seconds.

1466
01:48:22,033 --> 01:48:23,546
<i>[Pilot]</i>
<i>Flight time to drop point:</i>
<i>17 minutes.</i>

1467
01:48:30,061 --> 01:48:34,259
<i>Excuse me, General, sir,</i>
<i>with all due respect to you,</i>
<i>but what the fuck is going on?</i>

1468
01:48:34,341 --> 01:48:37,811
- You changed the coordinates,
didn't you, General?
- That's affirmative, Captain.

1469
01:48:37,901 --> 01:48:41,689
So now they think we're gutless,
the Feds? They think we won't
actually do it.

1470
01:48:41,781 --> 01:48:44,420
They're gonna come at us with
everything they got. Air and sea.

1471
01:48:44,501 --> 01:48:47,061
They're gonna bomb our ass
back to the Stone Age.

1472
01:48:47,141 --> 01:48:49,530
They don't know
we missed on purpose.

1473
01:48:49,621 --> 01:48:52,340
Great. We're not gutless.
We're incompetent.

1474
01:48:52,421 --> 01:48:54,252
That right?

1475
01:48:54,341 --> 01:48:56,901
I don't think
I like your tone, Captain.

1476
01:48:56,981 --> 01:49:00,576
We planned for this contingency.
Load the VX into the choppers,
take four hostages and evacuate.

1477
01:49:00,661 --> 01:49:02,970
<i>The consequences of our actions</i>
<i>I'll face alone.</i>

1478
01:49:03,061 --> 01:49:05,973
Excuse me, General, but
what about the fucking money?

1479
01:49:06,061 --> 01:49:08,450
There is no fucking money.
Mission's over.

1480
01:49:08,541 --> 01:49:10,259
Bullshit, it's over.

1481
01:49:10,341 --> 01:49:13,731
You're talking to a general,
soldier! Maintain discipline!

1482
01:49:13,821 --> 01:49:18,292
I'm not a soldier, Major. The day we
took hostages we became mercenaries.

1483
01:49:18,381 --> 01:49:23,011
<i>And mercenaries get paid.</i>
<i>I want my fucking money!</i>

1484
01:49:23,101 --> 01:49:26,537
This mission was based
on the threat of force.

1485
01:49:26,621 --> 01:49:29,215
<i>I'm not about to kill</i>
<i>80,000 innocent people.</i>

1486
01:49:29,301 --> 01:49:32,452
Do you think I'm
out of my fucking mind?

1487
01:49:32,541 --> 01:49:35,453
We bluffed. They called it.
The mission's over.

1488
01:49:38,541 --> 01:49:41,374
Who ever said anything
about bluffing, General?

1489
01:49:41,461 --> 01:49:44,134
Stand down, Captain.

1490
01:49:48,501 --> 01:49:51,573
Stand down, Captain!

1491
01:49:56,061 --> 01:50:00,657
<i>Major, I'm ordering you to take these</i>
<i>men to the choppers and evacuate.</i>

1492
01:50:00,741 --> 01:50:03,972
That's a simple
order, Major!

1493
01:50:04,061 --> 01:50:06,131
It's not so simple, Frank.

1494
01:50:06,221 --> 01:50:09,452
Sergeant Crisp,
secure the general.

1495
01:50:10,861 --> 01:50:13,659
I'm relieving you
of your command, sir.

1496
01:50:17,301 --> 01:50:19,940
Sergeant!

1497
01:50:26,301 --> 01:50:29,213
- I'll have that sidearm, sir.
- You mean this sidearm?

1498
01:50:37,781 --> 01:50:41,091
Major Baxter, you're either
with us or against us.

1499
01:50:46,461 --> 01:50:50,215
It has been the greatest honour
of my life to serve with you, General.

1500
01:50:54,341 --> 01:50:59,290
But like he said...
it's over.

1501
01:50:59,381 --> 01:51:01,656
[Grunts]

1502
01:51:16,101 --> 01:51:18,171
Let's get him.

1503
01:51:22,701 --> 01:51:24,612
Mason!

1504
01:51:26,661 --> 01:51:29,414
[Groaning]
My God, what have I done?

1505
01:51:29,501 --> 01:51:33,096
Where's the last rocket?
Where's the last rocket!

1506
01:51:34,821 --> 01:51:37,699
- Where's the last rocket?
- Lower lighthouse.

1507
01:51:37,781 --> 01:51:40,249
- Lower lighthouse!
- Go.

1508
01:51:52,221 --> 01:51:55,816
[Shouting]
Darrow, go to the lighthouse!
I'll take care of this fucker!

1509
01:52:01,861 --> 01:52:04,375
One, two, three!

1510
01:52:04,461 --> 01:52:06,975
Eat that!

1511
01:52:15,741 --> 01:52:17,652
[Groaning]

1512
01:52:19,701 --> 01:52:21,100
Did it.

1513
01:52:45,341 --> 01:52:47,809
[Grunts]

1514
01:52:48,981 --> 01:52:50,812
[Groans]

